metadata.title: Beechcraft Musketeer
aws::graph::propositions: Beechcraft Musketeer Aircraft Models
A23-19 is a Model 19 Beechcraft Musketeer.
A23-19 is a light cabin aircraft.
A23-19 can seat two or four people.
A23-19 has fixed tricycle landing gear.
A23-19 is powered by a Lycoming O-320-E2B piston engine.
A23-19 is powered by a Lycoming O-320-E2C piston engine.
A23-19 is powered by a Lycoming O-320-E3D piston engine.
The Lycoming engines for the A23-19 produce 150 hp (112 kW).
A23-19 has a gross weight of 2,200 lb (998 kg).
A23-19 was first certified on December 9, 1965.
A23-24 is a Beechcraft Musketeer.
A23-24 is a light cabin aircraft.
A23-24 can seat four or six people.
A23-24 has fixed tricycle landing gear.
A23-24 is powered by a Lycoming IO-360-A2B piston engine.
A23-24 is powered by a Lycoming IO-360-A2D piston engine.
A23-24 with a constant speed propeller is powered by a Lycoming IO-360-A1B piston engine.
A23-24 with a constant speed propeller is powered by a Lycoming IO-360-A1D piston engine.
The Lycoming engines for the A23-24 produce 200 hp (149 kW).
A23-24 has a gross weight of 2,550 lb (1,157 kg).
A23-24 was first certified on March 7, 1966.

text:
A23-19 (Model 19)
Two or four-seat light cabin aircraft, fixed tricycle landing gear, powered by a 150 hp (112 kW) Lycoming O-320-E2B, E2C or E3D piston engine, gross weight of 2,200 lb (998 kg), first certified December 9, 1965.
A23-24
Four or six-seat light cabin aircraft, fixed tricycle landing gear, powered by a 200 hp (149 kW) Lycoming IO-360-A2B or A2D, or when equipped with a constant speed propeller a Lycoming IO-360-A1B or A1D piston engine, gross weight of 2,550 lb (1,157 kg), first certified March 7, 1966.
